<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>post boat • post ship</xh5><p> <i>post boat—</i>a ship conveying mail or travelers, especially on a regular route: We have the choice of the <u>post boat</u> tomorrow, which takes a limited number of passengers, or the bigger boat on Saturday.</p><p> <i>post ship</i>—(UK hist.) a Royal Navy ship of not less than twenty guns: Every ship of twenty guns or more was a <u>postship</u>, and a man was ordinarily said to be posted, that is, appointed to command a ship.</p> </entry>
